wiki.summary: On “Yebba’s Heartbreak,” Drake enlists Grammy-award winning singer and songwriter Yebba for a romantic interlude. The track, which does not feature vocals from Drake, is a running theme throughout his albums with PARTYNEXTDOOR and Majid Jordan having previously provided interludes for his records (“Wednesday Night Interlude” and “Summers Over Interlude” respectively) as well as several interludes featured on Drake’s 2017 project More Life, such as “Jorja Interlude”, “4422” and “Skepta Interlude”. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: On “Yebba’s Heartbreak,” Drake enlists Grammy-award winning singer and songwriter Yebba for a romantic interlude. The track, which does not feature vocals from Drake, is a running theme throughout his albums with PARTYNEXTDOOR and Majid Jordan having previously provided interludes for his records (“Wednesday Night Interlude” and “Summers Over Interlude” respectively) as well as several interludes featured on Drake’s 2017 project More Life, such as “Jorja Interlude”, “4422” and “Skepta Interlude”. “Yebba’s Heartbreak” debuted and peaked at #24 Billboard Hot 100 for the charting week ending September 18, 2021.
